n=top bgcolor=#000000 class=headings><font color=#A0B0E0>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usunthasbayne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sunthas Bayne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 11:04:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1998.topic>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.webpak.net/~njb/emblemsm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Testing on Greys</span><hr size=1> When I wack a really low grey with a normal hit I get some number. With the Hammer I like to use that number is 320. As I wack higher and higher greys it stays 320 for awhile then it starts to drop and very a little when I get to greys that are very high greys.<br><br>Then I start doing greens and my Varience widens a bit more and rarely do I see a hit for 320, but 300 is not uncommon. <br><br>As I move up through the blues and yellows the Varience widens a bit more and a 300 becomes much more rare.<br><br>As I move into oranges, reds and purples I rarely see numbers anywhere close to max.<br><br>Now if I do styles on the mobs and repeat the process I notice that those styles (all other things equal) remain the same percentage of damage through out the color spectrum. So if it does 60% more damage with a style on a level -0- grey bumping me up to ~512 damage. If when I get to the reds I'm only doing about 100 normal damage then with styles I'm doing about 160 damage. <br><br>Perfectly scaled. What performing the tests on level -0- greys does is take out the varience and take out all influence from str, dex, qua, and con of the weapon. <br><br>Furthermore those that do tons of RVR will notice that if someone is sitting and very lightly armored they will do close to the same damage on them (but not more) that they do on a level -0- grey.<br><br>I know there are lots of thoughts out there about why testing on level -0- greys is a very bad method to use, and I wanna hear those objections and clear them up, or adjust my thinking if its indeed invalid. <p><table style=filter:glow(color=#FFFFFFstrength=3><font size=1 color=#000000 face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif> Sunthas Bayne<BR>Firbolg Hero<br>Guild Leader - Dei Gratia</table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uscrappinak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scrappinak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 11:11:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1998.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Testing on Greys</span><hr size=1> It's just about as effective as doing real-world tests assuming a frictionless plane or assuming perpetual motion -- ie pointless. If things were really that simple we wouldn't need the tests in the first place.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=majin>Majin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 11:16:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1998.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Testing on Greys</span><hr size=1> Yeah since the styles (like CS) are scaled upon weapon damage you need a high weaponskill to get a high perforate or whatsoever against a higher con mob. This doesnt bother you on lower con mobs. <p><img border=0 src=http://members.tripod.de/majin_mlf/midgard_ownz_small.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugrinkle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grinkle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 11:36:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1998.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://sigstuff1.homestead.com/files/Lute_pic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Testing on Greys</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> ie pointless.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>I disagree.  For instance, I want to know if my L30 quest bow has the potential to do more damage or less damage than my Runewood Great Recurve.  I can see the DPS and speed, but I'm not sure what the +3 recurve and +7 Dex might do for me.<br><br>I one-shot a low grey with each bow, question answered in about 10 seconds with no risk / time wasted.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uchemistrius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chemistrius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 12:51:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1998.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.clearpicture.com/images/mists.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Testing on Greys</span><hr size=1> heh. That's how I used to compare weapons I would get...Just go smack a few mobs in the nearest noob zone and just compare the immediate results.  It's not a perfect science, but it does give you a quick baseline to comapre all your weaps on. <p><CENTER><TABLE cellpadding=5 cellspacing=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><TD colspan=2><HR></TD></TR><TR valign=top><TD align=right><FONT Size=5><B><u>Chemistrius Ul'Veldrin   </u></B></FONT><BR><FONT size=-1>60<sup>th</Sup> Season Dark Elf Assassin<BR>Officer of Requiem of Souls</FONT></TD><TD><FONT size=-2>It will be a hard life.<BR>One without remorse, without reward, without regret.<BR>A path will be placed before you, the choice is yours alone.<BR>Do what you think you cannot do.<BR>It will be a hard life, but you will find out who you are.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD colspan=2><HR></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usunthasbayne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sunthas Bayne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 1:15:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1998.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Testing on Greys</span><hr size=1> Well, non-cs styles aren't scaled up with weapon damage.<br><br>I don't think CS styles are scaled up with weapon damage either.<br><br>Have you tested a 1.5dps weapon on a low Green yet with a Critical Strike like PA? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uchemistrius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chemistrius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 3:33:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1998.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Testing on Greys</span><hr size=1> I'm pretty sure that CS damage does scale with weapon damage.  I can recall a while back I had 2 similar weapons (I do forget what they were, but they had almost the same dps and they had the same con but the delay's were different)  I would PA mobs with one a few times (the same mobs mind you, usually tiny bear types) then I would repeat with the other weapon.  The slower delayed weapon (ie higher damage) always hit for like 30 or 40 more damage.  now that was in the 20's so it didn't make a huge difference, but it was a difference all the same.<br><br>blah blah blah I'm starting to babble.<br><br>It does make a diff, just not a huge one iirc.  Just try it for yourself <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usunthasbayne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sunthas Bayne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 4:21:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1998.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.webpak.net/~njb/emblemsm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Testing on Greys</span><hr size=1> Chem thats how styles work for Large Weapons. Some people are reporting that Critical Strikes seem completely different. Your example only shows that delay matters, not that PA damage scales with weapon damage. <br><br>Try the test again with a 1.5 dps weapon. <p><table style=filter:glow(color=#FFFFFFstrength=3><font size=1 color=#000000 face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif> Sunthas Bayne<BR>Firbolg Hero<br>Guild Leader - Dei Gratia</table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usunthasbayne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sunthas Bayne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 4:33:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1998.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Testing on Greys</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>- Damage clamp of spell damages raised to be comparable with damage clamps from melee attacks. These should only come into play when you smack low level targets (grays). Now caster max damage against low level players and monsters should be about the same as melee max damage. <br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.camelotherald.com/more/183.php">www.camelotherald.com/more/183.php</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br>Clamp probably means Cap just mispelled... twice... unless clamp means something I'm unaware of.<br><br>This quote seems to be confirmation that hitting a low level grey is a true measure of your maximum damage potential. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucaithcaidh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caith Caidh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/2/02 2:13:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1998.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Testing on Greys</span><hr size=1> You cannot test skill issues on low greys.  Because the con is so low, you will hit the cap even using a weapon that you have less ability in using.  So you'll get a damage cap that is reliant on the weapon and the style used, rather than your ability to use said weapon.  As an example, I wanted to test to see how a staff would work as a CS weapon for me, as it is dex based.  Well, I find a staff and a weapon in my current weaponspec with similar dps, and perf the same grey mob.  The staff will cap with more damage, however if I actually fight a non-grey mob, my specced weapon will just about always outdamage the staff.  Particularly when there are many variables involved OTHER than the weapons themselves, and styles themselves, greys are unreliable.  In the staff example, we need to somehow account for both the effects of weapon spec, and the effects of the stat base as pertains to the average CS damage we will do on an even con.  In other words - Yes, it will tell you what your maximum damage is.   However, it won't tell you how near you will come to actually doing that maximum damage against a tougher opponent.<br><br> <p><IMG SRC="http://www.dopplex.net/sigfile2.jpg" ALT="Caith Caidh, 35th Season Nightshade, An Claidheamh Soluis" ALIGN="middle"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uubergnome563.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ubergnome563</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/2/02 4:11:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1998.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> Grays are good for finding out absolute caps, such as on a sitting target in rvr.  No way will anybody non crit perf somebody who is standing (or green or higher) con for what you hit a level 0 for, but it does allow you to see your absolute limitations with respect to people sitting and gray cons.  If somebody is sitting, and i think they have more than x (being my perf cap on a gray) hp, i dont attack them unless solo.  <br><br>Like if i wanted to compare a thrust style to garrot, i would first find the max cap on both styles, and then experiment on a mob paying close attention to the +bonuses and overall damage.  generally I find it pretty reliable to predict which style will do more damage / end ratio by testing on level 0s and going with what has the higher cap.<br><br>It doesnt give you any useful data as per fighting evenish con objects, but it does give you a reasonable ability to predict the differnece between 2 or more styles, and the limitations upon you in an ideal situation <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showMessage?topicID=2006.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showMessage?topicID=1995.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1998.topic&index=10><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a 